-- Carter Holt Said to Complete NZ$1.45 Billion Loan With KEB
-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s   a n d   W e n d y   M o c k
-- 2012-02-03T08:02:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/carter-holt-said-to-complete-nz-1-45-billion-loan-with-keb.html
Carter Holt Harvey Ltd. (CAH) , the wood
products firm owned by  New Zealand  billionaire  Graeme Hart ,
completed general syndication of a NZ$1.45 billion ($1.2
billion) loan after receiving a commitment from Korea Exchange
Bank, said a person familiar with the matter.  Credit Suisse Group AG, which arranged the loan, underwrote
the facility along with  Australia  & New Zealand Banking Group
Ltd.,  Bank of New Zealand ,  Commonwealth Bank of Australia , HSBC
Holdings Plc, Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp. and Westpac Banking
Corp., the person said. BOS International, Mizuho Corporate Bank
Ltd., and Rabobank International also joined as senior lenders.
BOS International is a unit of Lloyds Banking Group Plc.  To contact the reporters on this story:
